
2.CLASS SELECTOR-A class selector is referred to a CSS Class or simply a class.

NOTE:Class names cannot start witth a number, contain spaces butt can contain hyphens and underscores.

EXAMPLE:External Class Selector

.custom-bg-blue {
background-color:blue;
}

.custom-bg-yellow{
background-color:yellow;
}

.custom-text-white{
color:white;
}

Other Notes:

Make sure to include the dot (.) in front of the class name.

EXAMPLE 2:Inline Class Selector

<p class="custom-bg-blue">

...

</p>

<p class="custom-bg-yellow">

...

</p>


<p class="custom-bg-blue custom-text-white">
...
</p>

